body:
@ngupta23, there was a bug we fixed, where pipeline concatenation and automatic vectorization (across instances) were done in the wrong order, it should have been "vectorize first, then concatenate", but it actually happened the other way round, with whether vectorization happened determined by the first pipeline element.

Vectorizing the reconciler would make it trivial (a simple passthrough), potentially leading to the behaviour you describe.

Hence, you could help us by checking whether the problem still persists on current `main`, it could have already been fixed by https://github.com/alan-turing-institute/sktime/pull/2644 which was merged two days ago.
